com.google.api.ads.dfp.lib

Class DfpUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.api.ads.dfp.lib.DfpUser

  • public class DfpUser
extends java.lang.Object
    The DfpUser class contains all needed information to authenticate a user as well as generate a valid service for that user. The way in which a service is generated is performed as:

    DfpUser user = new DfpUser(email, password, networkCode, applicationName);
    ServiceInterface service = user.getService(DfpService.version.serviceName);

    The interface <Service>Interface should match that described by DfpService.version.serviceName or else a ServiceException will be thrown. For example, if you wished to get the service InventoryService and you referenced this service by DfpService.v201308.INVENTORY_SERVICE, your import of InventoryServiceInterface should be from the package com.google.api.ads.dfp.v201308.

    Author:
    api.arogal@gmail.com (Adam Rogal)
